Cloud Support Engineer Project | Azure • AWS • Monitoring • Incident Response

📌 Overview

This project simulates a real-world enterprise cloud environment focused on monitoring, security, and incident response across hybrid infrastructure.

Built to demonstrate hands-on skills required for:

• Cloud Support Engineer
• NOC Analyst
• Junior Cloud Engineer

🎯 Objectives

• Deploy and manage cloud infrastructure in Microsoft Azure and AWS
• Implement monitoring and alerting pipelines
• Enforce least-privilege access (RBAC/IAM)
• Simulate real-world incidents and response workflows
• Integrate SIEM tools for log analysis and detection

🏗️ Architecture

Azure VNet (10.0.0.0/16)
│
├── Subnet: Frontend (10.0.1.0/24)
│   └── Windows VM (RDP Access)
│
├── Subnet: Backend (10.0.2.0/24)
│   └── Linux VM (SSH Access)
│
├── Network Security Groups (NSGs)
│   ├── Allow: RDP (3389) from trusted IP
│   ├── Allow: SSH (22)
│   └── Deny: All other inbound traffic
│
├── Azure AD (Entra ID)
│   ├── RBAC Roles (Reader / Contributor)
│   └── User Provisioning & Access Control
│
├── Monitoring & Logging
│   ├── Azure Monitor + Log Analytics
│   ├── AWS CloudWatch
│   ├── Splunk / Datadog Integration
│
└── Alerting System
    ├── CPU Utilization Alerts
    ├── Failed Login Attempts
    └── VM Availability Alerts
    
